text: The laughing gull (Leucophaeus atricilla) is a type of gull in North and South America. Laughing gulls are omnivores, they eat plants and animals. == Description == The laughing gull breeds on the Atlantic coast of North America, the Caribbean, and northern parts of South America. == References == Category:Charadriiformes Category:Birds of North America Category:Birds of South America
title: Laughing gull
